OL,3,CBirmingham Council to settle equal pay
OL,4,Cclaim after bankruptcy, sources say
OL,6,FThe legal claims in Birmingham
OL,7,Fcompared the predominantly female
OL,8,Froles to those in waste and refuse,
OL,9,Fcarried out primarily by men. Two
OL,10,Fissues were highlighted - firstly that
OL,11,Fthe men had been offered "task and
OL,12,Ffinish" in which they were paid per
OL,13,Ftask instead of per hour. As a result,
OL,14,Fthey could go home much earlier than
OL,15,Fthe women working in care or catering,
OL,16,For they could overtime, also
OL,17,Funavailable to the women.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
